31constexpr size_t kRedForFecHeaderLength = 1;
32
33// This controls the maximum amount of excess overhead (actual - target)
34// allowed in order to trigger EncodeFec(), before |params_.max_fec_frames|
35// is reached. Overhead here is defined as relative to number of media packets.
36constexpr int kMaxExcessOverhead = 50; // Q8.
37
38// This is the minimum number of media packets required (above some protection
39// level) in order to trigger EncodeFec(), before |params_.max_fec_frames| is
40// reached.
41constexpr size_t kMinMediaPackets = 4;
42
43// Threshold on the received FEC protection level, above which we enforce at
44// least |kMinMediaPackets| packets for the FEC code. Below this
45// threshold |kMinMediaPackets| is set to default value of 1.
46//
47// The range is between 0 and 255, where 255 corresponds to 100% overhead
48// (relative to the number of protected media packets).
49constexpr uint8_t kHighProtectionThreshold = 80;
50
51// This threshold is used to adapt the |kMinMediaPackets| threshold, based
52// on the average number of packets per frame seen so far. When there are few
53// packets per frame (as given by this threshold), at least
54// |kMinMediaPackets| + 1 packets are sent to the FEC code.
55constexpr float kMinMediaPacketsAdaptationThreshold = 2.0f;
56
57// At construction time, we don't know the SSRC that is used for the generated
58// FEC packets, but we still need to give it to the ForwardErrorCorrection ctor
59// to be used in the decoding.
60// TODO(brandtr): Get rid of this awkwardness by splitting
61// ForwardErrorCorrection in two objects -- one encoder and one decoder.
62constexpr uint32_t kUnknownSsrc = 0;
63
64} // namespace
65
66UlpfecGenerator::Params::Params() = default;
67UlpfecGenerator::Params::Params(FecProtectionParams delta_params,
68 FecProtectionParams keyframe_params)
69 : delta_params(delta_params), keyframe_params(keyframe_params) {}
70
71UlpfecGenerator::UlpfecGenerator(int red_payload_type,
72 int ulpfec_payload_type,
73 Clock* clock)
74 : red_payload_type_(red_payload_type),
75 ulpfec_payload_type_(ulpfec_payload_type),
76 clock_(clock),
77 fec_(ForwardErrorCorrection::CreateUlpfec(kUnknownSsrc)),
78 num_protected_frames_(0),
79 min_num_media_packets_(1),
80 media_contains_keyframe_(false),
81 fec_bitrate_(/*max_window_size_ms=*/1000, RateStatistics::kBpsScale) {}
82
83// Used by FlexFecSender, payload types are unused.
84UlpfecGenerator::UlpfecGenerator(std::unique_ptr<ForwardErrorCorrection> fec,
85 Clock* clock)
86 : red_payload_type_(0),
87 ulpfec_payload_type_(0),
88 clock_(clock),
89 fec_(std::move(fec)),
90 num_protected_frames_(0),
91 min_num_media_packets_(1),
92 media_contains_keyframe_(false),
93 fec_bitrate_(/*max_window_size_ms=*/1000, RateStatistics::kBpsScale) {}
94
95UlpfecGenerator::~UlpfecGenerator() = default;
96
97void UlpfecGenerator::SetProtectionParameters(
98 const FecProtectionParams& delta_params,
99 const FecProtectionParams& key_params) {
100 RTC_DCHECK_GE(delta_params.fec_rate, 0);
101 RTC_DCHECK_LE(delta_params.fec_rate, 255);
102 RTC_DCHECK_GE(key_params.fec_rate, 0);
103 RTC_DCHECK_LE(key_params.fec_rate, 255);
104 // Store the new params and apply them for the next set of FEC packets being
105 // produced.
106 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
107 pending_params_.emplace(delta_params, key_params);
108}
109
110void UlpfecGenerator::AddPacketAndGenerateFec(const RtpPacketToSend& packet) {
111 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
112 RTC_DCHECK(generated_fec_packets_.empty());
113
114 {
115 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
116 if (pending_params_) {
117 current_params_ = *pending_params_;
118 pending_params_.reset();
119
120 if (CurrentParams().fec_rate > kHighProtectionThreshold) {
121 min_num_media_packets_ = kMinMediaPackets;
122 } else {
123 min_num_media_packets_ = 1;
124 }
125 }
126 }
127
128 if (packet.is_key_frame()) {
129 media_contains_keyframe_ = true;
130 }
131 const bool complete_frame = packet.Marker();
132 if (media_packets_.size() < kUlpfecMaxMediaPackets) {
133 // Our packet masks can only protect up to |kUlpfecMaxMediaPackets| packets.
134 auto fec_packet = std::make_unique<ForwardErrorCorrection::Packet>();
135 fec_packet->data = packet.Buffer();
136 media_packets_.push_back(std::move(fec_packet));
137
138 // Keep a copy of the last RTP packet, so we can copy the RTP header
139 // from it when creating newly generated ULPFEC+RED packets.
140 RTC_DCHECK_GE(packet.headers_size(), kRtpHeaderSize);
141 last_media_packet_ = packet;
142 }
143
144 if (complete_frame) {
145 ++num_protected_frames_;
146 }
147
148 auto params = CurrentParams();
149
150 // Produce FEC over at most |params_.max_fec_frames| frames, or as soon as:
151 // (1) the excess overhead (actual overhead - requested/target overhead) is
152 // less than |kMaxExcessOverhead|, and
153 // (2) at least |min_num_media_packets_| media packets is reached.
154 if (complete_frame &&
155 (num_protected_frames_ >= params.max_fec_frames ||
156 (ExcessOverheadBelowMax() && MinimumMediaPacketsReached()))) {
157 // We are not using Unequal Protection feature of the parity erasure code.
158 constexpr int kNumImportantPackets = 0;
159 constexpr bool kUseUnequalProtection = false;
160 fec_->EncodeFec(media_packets_, params.fec_rate, kNumImportantPackets,
161 kUseUnequalProtection, params.fec_mask_type,
162 &generated_fec_packets_);
163 if (generated_fec_packets_.empty()) {
164 ResetState();
165 }
166 }
167}
168
169bool UlpfecGenerator::ExcessOverheadBelowMax() const {
170 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
171
172 return ((Overhead() - CurrentParams().fec_rate) < kMaxExcessOverhead);
173}
174
175bool UlpfecGenerator::MinimumMediaPacketsReached() const {
176 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
177 float average_num_packets_per_frame =
178 static_cast<float>(media_packets_.size()) / num_protected_frames_;
179 int num_media_packets = static_cast<int>(media_packets_.size());
180 if (average_num_packets_per_frame < kMinMediaPacketsAdaptationThreshold) {
181 return num_media_packets >= min_num_media_packets_;
182 } else {
183 // For larger rates (more packets/frame), increase the threshold.
184 // TODO(brandtr): Investigate what impact this adaptation has.
185 return num_media_packets >= min_num_media_packets_ + 1;
186 }
187}
188
189const FecProtectionParams& UlpfecGenerator::CurrentParams() const {
190 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
191 return media_contains_keyframe_ ? current_params_.keyframe_params
192 : current_params_.delta_params;
193}
194
195size_t UlpfecGenerator::MaxPacketOverhead() const {
196 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
197 return fec_->MaxPacketOverhead();
198}
199
200std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> UlpfecGenerator::GetFecPackets() {
201 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
202 if (generated_fec_packets_.empty()) {
203 return std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>>();
204 }
205
206 // Wrap FEC packet (including FEC headers) in a RED packet. Since the
207 // FEC packets in |generated_fec_packets_| don't have RTP headers, we
208 // reuse the header from the last media packet.
209 RTC_CHECK(last_media_packet_.has_value());
210 last_media_packet_->SetPayloadSize(0);
211
212 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> fec_packets;
213 fec_packets.reserve(generated_fec_packets_.size());
214
215 size_t total_fec_size_bytes = 0;
216 for (const auto* fec_packet : generated_fec_packets_) {
217 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> red_packet =
218 std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(*last_media_packet_);
219 red_packet->SetPayloadType(red_payload_type_);
220 red_packet->SetMarker(false);
221 uint8_t* payload_buffer = red_packet->SetPayloadSize(
222 kRedForFecHeaderLength + fec_packet->data.size());
223 // Primary RED header with F bit unset.
224 // See https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2198#section-3
225 payload_buffer[0] = ulpfec_payload_type_; // RED header.
226 memcpy(&payload_buffer[1], fec_packet->data.data(),
227 fec_packet->data.size());
228 total_fec_size_bytes += red_packet->size();
229 red_packet->set_packet_type(RtpPacketMediaType::kForwardErrorCorrection);
230 red_packet->set_allow_retransmission(false);
231 red_packet->set_is_red(true);
232 red_packet->set_fec_protect_packet(false);
233 fec_packets.push_back(std::move(red_packet));
234 }
235
236 ResetState();
237
238 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
239 fec_bitrate_.Update(total_fec_size_bytes, clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
240
241 return fec_packets;
242}
243
244DataRate UlpfecGenerator::CurrentFecRate() const {
245 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
246 return DataRate::BitsPerSec(
247 fec_bitrate_.Rate(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()).value_or(0));
248}
249
250int UlpfecGenerator::Overhead() const {
251 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
252 RTC_DCHECK(!media_packets_.empty());
253 int num_fec_packets =
254 fec_->NumFecPackets(media_packets_.size(), CurrentParams().fec_rate);
255
256 // Return the overhead in Q8.
257 return (num_fec_packets << 8) / media_packets_.size();
258}
259
260void UlpfecGenerator::ResetState() {
261 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&race_checker_);
262 media_packets_.clear();
263 last_media_packet_.reset();
264 generated_fec_packets_.clear();
265 num_protected_frames_ = 0;
266 media_contains_keyframe_ = false;
267}
